  "text": "For immunochemistry test of clinical samples, briefly, formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded samples were prepared as 4-µm-thick sections as previously described [CITATION_1] . The sections were incubated with primary antibodies against CD133 (ab19898; Abcam) and ALDH1 (sc-166362, Santa Cruz Biotechnology, Inc.) at 4˚C overnight, and subjected to be incubated with the appropriate secondary antibody for 30 min at room temperature. IHC staining results in each sample was scored using semiquantitative scoring system, taking into consideration the staining intensity obtained and the proportion of positive cells observed.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "17630422"
